From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Xianglong Kong <xkong@anaconda.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] openmp/module: drop premature set_property on runtime/src

Note: Patch generated with AI assistance.

LLVM 22 refactored Fortran module generation into openmp/module/, which
is added via add_subdirectory(module) in openmp/CMakeLists.txt BEFORE
add_subdirectory(runtime). The line below tries to attach an
ADDITIONAL_MAKE_CLEAN_FILES property to the runtime/src binary
directory, but at the time module/CMakeLists.txt is processed CMake
hasn't yet visited runtime/src, so the call fails with:

    CMake Error at module/CMakeLists.txt:60 (set_property):
      set_property DIRECTORY scope provided but requested directory was
      not found. This could be because the directory argument was invalid
      or, it is valid but has not been processed yet.

This only triggers on platforms where CMAKE_Fortran_COMPILER_LOADED is
true, i.e. Windows in our build matrix. Since the property is only a
`make clean` hint for an intermediate omp_lib object file (and on
Windows we use Ninja, not make), removing it has no functional impact.

---
 openmp/module/CMakeLists.txt | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/openmp/module/CMakeLists.txt b/openmp/module/CMakeLists.txt
index 0000000000000..0000000000000 100644
--- a/openmp/module/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/openmp/module/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -57,6 +57,5 @@ elseif (CMAKE_Fortran_COMPILER_LOADED)
             ${LIBOMP_CONFIGURED_FFLAGS} ${LIBOMP_FORTRAN_SOURCE_FILE} "-J${CMAKE_CURRENT_BINARY_DIR}/../runtime/src"
     DEPENDS "${CMAKE_CURRENT_BINARY_DIR}/${LIBOMP_FORTRAN_SOURCE_FILE}"
   )
-  set_property(DIRECTORY "${CMAKE_CURRENT_BINARY_DIR}/../runtime/src" PROPERTY ADDITIONAL_MAKE_CLEAN_FILES "omp_lib${CMAKE_C_OUTPUT_EXTENSION}")
   set(BUILD_FORTRAN_MODULES True)
 endif ()

